reviews.review_text: Paris J'attendais ce moment avec impatience enfin il est arrivé Merci beaucoup Pour moi c'était mon dernier concert du DEAD

What a time.... We were guests of the tour manager Mr. Sears at these Euro shows... We had to simply go to the will call window to pick up our seats at all of the different cities played.... That particular day we made our way on the metro to the Zenith for the show. The vibe outside was just great, almost unreal, The Dead in Paris, what could be better... Well, the show was.... It was one of the louder shows I had seen to that point, and I had been to quite a few... From the beginning to the end, the energy level was really high, as was the quality of music. Loved the Paris shows on this tour. Other shows we saw in London, and Hamberg were great as well... They all had their own vibe... All in all, one of the better times in my life...

Fantastic show Got lucky. The tour coincided with my planned backpacking trip in Europe.  The venue was great.  Maybe 4500 people.  Level above the floor was standing room, wide cat walk type balcony around perimeter of the theatre.  Plenty of room to dance.  The energy was immense and it was probably the best Dead show I ever saw.  Certainly felt that way after show.  Got lucky again when we met tapers in Salzburg who gave as DAT quality tapes of the show to enjoy for the rest of the trip.  Tapes confirmed our experience, it was a smoking show.
